1
00:00:00,810 --> 00:00:03,140
You know Mr. Kang Nam Bong
and Mr. Oh Bok Gil, right?

2
00:00:04,010 --> 00:00:05,880
I'm here regarding a car accident.

3
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:07,750
I heard about that.

4
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:10,120
Please, have a seat.

5
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:12,680
Please bring us some tea.

6
00:00:20,090 --> 00:00:21,090
Please, have some tea.

7
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:23,730
Thank you.

8
00:00:32,740 --> 00:00:35,970
I have a few questions for you.

9
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:39,580
And what would those be?

10
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:43,680
Before Mr. Oh Bok Gil
called Ms. Oh Jang Mi,

11
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:48,090
the last person he spoke with was you.

12
00:00:49,590 --> 00:00:50,960
What was the nature of your conversation?

13
00:00:51,620 --> 00:00:52,820
He called me.

14
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:56,930
He said I hadn't been by for side dishes
and offered to bring some over.

15
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:01,300
I was in the middle of a meeting
and very busy,

16
00:01:01,830 --> 00:01:04,400
so I told him it wasn't a good time.

17
00:01:04,570 --> 00:01:08,540
So you didn't see him, then?

18
00:01:09,170 --> 00:01:10,180
That's right.

19
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:20,920
I confirmed with her secretary
and other staff...

20
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:23,590
that she was in her office the whole time.

21
00:01:24,890 --> 00:01:25,890
Okay, got it.

22
00:01:29,690 --> 00:01:31,800
Manager Lee, I was just looking for you.

23
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:32,930
Did my mom say anything?

24
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:37,270
The detective can't see Seo Rin.
She looks just like Oh Jang Mi.

25
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:39,870
I asked if my mom said anything.

26
00:01:40,270 --> 00:01:41,270
Goodness.

27
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,040
That she was looking for you?

28
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:45,480
If you think of anything else,
please give us a call.

29
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:48,480
Actually, there was something
I wanted to ask you, too.

30
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:50,080
Come on. Let's talk somewhere else.

31
00:01:50,220 --> 00:01:52,250
What? What is it?

32
00:01:52,250 --> 00:01:54,020
Hey, let go of me.

33
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:01,930
The control room? You went there too?

34
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,900
The CCTV malfunctioned that day.

35
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,700
All the cameras in the parking lot
were off.

36
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:08,870
Really?

37
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:11,140
But the lobby cameras were working fine.

38
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,740
Did you come looking for me
because you thought that was weird?

39
00:02:13,810 --> 00:02:17,210
Yes. There have been too many solicitors
at the hotel lately,

40
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,810
and I felt we needed
to get it under control.

41
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:21,510
Actually, I was already planning to boost
our security on the CEO's orders.

42
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:23,310
Okay.

43
00:02:24,820 --> 00:02:28,290
By the way, why did that detective
come to see my mom?

44
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:32,520
I wouldn't know about that.

45
00:02:36,290 --> 00:02:37,360
What? Wait a minute.

46
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:41,730
The bouquet is ready?
All right, I'm on my way.

47
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:44,370
It's a very important bouquet,
so please handle it with care.

48
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:47,340
It's for Chef Kang.

49
00:02:47,610 --> 00:02:50,170
I mean, General Manager Kang.
I ordered a bouquet to congratulate him.

50
00:02:51,210 --> 00:02:52,210
Bye.

51
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:33,180
Here's the bouquet you ordered.

52
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:36,050
What did that detective say earlier?

53
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:40,260
It seems some man came here...

54
00:03:40,330 --> 00:03:41,790
and was in an accident afterward.

55
00:03:41,790 --> 00:03:43,630
An accident? What kind?

56
00:03:43,860 --> 00:03:44,960
A car accident.

57
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:49,330
Apparently, he was in a car accident
out in the countryside and was badly hurt.

58
00:03:50,070 --> 00:03:51,540
Why cause a scene here...

59
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:53,870
over an accident
that happened out in the countryside?

60
00:03:54,410 --> 00:03:56,740
How annoying. You can go.

61
00:04:07,020 --> 00:04:09,790
He must be exhausted
after being questioned all night.

62
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:12,960
What?

63
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,790
The victim's son?

64
00:04:15,260 --> 00:04:16,890
What's with this car accident?

65
00:04:17,930 --> 00:04:20,000
Could this have something to do
with Jun Ho's family?

66
00:04:20,370 --> 00:04:22,430
Is that why the detectives
came to our hotel?

67
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,240
But then, why did they meet with my mom?

68
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:29,010
Hey.

69
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,140
They've tracked your father's phone,

70
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:35,280
and they said the last cell tower
it pinged before the crash...

71
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,310
was at Dream Hotel.

72
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:37,720
Dad was at Dream Hotel?

73
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:41,450
That's right. Dad asked me for
CEO Chae's phone number.

74
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:42,820
By the way,

75
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:44,520
do you have CEO Chae's phone number?

76
00:04:44,990 --> 00:04:45,990
The CEO? Why?

77
00:04:46,590 --> 00:04:50,400
What do you mean, "why?"
She hasn't been in for side dishes lately.

78
00:04:50,460 --> 00:04:53,670
I was just going to call and check on her
for customer service.

79
00:04:55,330 --> 00:04:58,340
Then maybe he did meet
with CEO Chae after all.

80
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,940
What did the detective say?

81
00:05:01,210 --> 00:05:02,840
He questioned CEO Chae as well,

82
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:05,010
but she never met with your father.

83
00:05:05,910 --> 00:05:08,950
Then if Dad didn't see CEO Chae,

84
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:10,650
why was he at the accident scene?

85
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:13,520
I just don't understand how he ended up
all the way out there.

86
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:17,120
When you last spoke with your father,
did he mention anything?

87
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,290
He was about to say something, but...

88
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,730
He said he saw someone
who looked just like me.

89
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,830
He saw someone who looked like you?

90
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:32,840
Yes. But he said he just
saw them on the street.

91
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:35,240
So that was the last thing he said?

92
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:38,110
No, not exactly.

93
00:05:38,180 --> 00:05:39,880
Hey! Who do you think you are?

94
00:05:40,010 --> 00:05:42,180
What gives you the right to weasel in?

95
00:05:42,380 --> 00:05:43,550
You think we want you here?

96
00:05:43,610 --> 00:05:45,120
I'm just as frustrated as you are.

97
00:05:45,180 --> 00:05:48,050
We need to find out what happened.

98
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,890
What about my dad's cell phone?
Was it found?

99
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:52,720
No, not yet.

100
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:56,430
The police searched the whole scene
but couldn't find it.

101
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:59,330
But why was the hotel's CCTV turned off
due to a malfunction of all times?

102
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,730
That doesn't make any sense
for a hotel that size?

103
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,400
Nothing about this is adding up.

104
00:06:03,470 --> 00:06:06,270
You're right.
If your father was at Dream Hotel,

105
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:10,210
how on earth did he get all the way
to the countryside where the accident was?

106
00:06:10,610 --> 00:06:11,740
It's a big question.

107
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,250
Who he met for a drink during that time...

108
00:06:14,810 --> 00:06:16,250
is another thing we have to uncover.

109
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:18,750
Since Dad didn't take his truck,

110
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:20,650
I'll have to check...

111
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:22,550
all the transportation options
around the hotel.

112
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:25,920
Way to make me feel awkward
for congratulating you.

113
00:06:25,990 --> 00:06:28,330
I know very well you're not the type
to feel awkward.

114
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:33,800
It's no fun when you know me so well.

115
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,900
A game?

116
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:39,940
Do you really think I'm playing
some kind of game with you, Director Ma?

117
00:06:40,940 --> 00:06:42,310
Don't get so defensive.

118
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:44,080
My congratulations are sincere.

119
00:06:44,410 --> 00:06:46,380
Please accept the flowers.

120
00:06:46,580 --> 00:06:48,080
Besides, I have to be somewhere,

121
00:06:48,150 --> 00:06:49,750
so I can't entertain you any longer,
General Manager Kang.

122
00:06:55,490 --> 00:06:56,550
What do you think you're doing?

123
00:06:56,690 --> 00:06:59,620
What's a celebration without a kiss?

124
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:01,160
It's like cake without frosting,
Grandpa said.

125
00:07:02,890 --> 00:07:04,100
Unbelievable.

126
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:10,700
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

127
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:13,910
Mom,

128
00:07:13,910 --> 00:07:16,870
Dad will be back home and healthy
before you know it. Stop crying now.

129
00:07:17,010 --> 00:07:18,980
I miss Bok Gil.

130
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:21,410
Where did Bok Gil go?

131
00:07:21,910 --> 00:07:23,610
Bok Gil's not here.

132
00:07:24,350 --> 00:07:27,490
Jang Mi's gone too. Jang Mi!

133
00:07:28,290 --> 00:07:29,490
- Jang Mi!
- Mom.

134
00:07:29,890 --> 00:07:31,020
I'm here, Mom.
It's your daughter, Jang Mi.

135
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,960
I heard you were crying
because I was gone.

136
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:36,890
Jang Mi is here. Oh, you're so pretty.

137
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:39,960
It's okay, Mom. It's okay.

138
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:41,930
But...

139
00:07:42,470 --> 00:07:43,730
what am I going to do about Dad?

140
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:46,370
What should I do, Mom?

141
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:56,510
Oh Jang Mi keeps calling me.
What should I do?

142
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:58,250
Have you just been ignoring her calls?

143
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:00,320
She only calls when there's trouble.

144
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:03,420
It would probably be best
to take one of her calls.

145
00:08:03,690 --> 00:08:04,760
You think so, right?

146
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:09,260
She's probably already heard
that the police were here to question me,

147
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:13,700
so pretending I don't know
and avoiding her will raise suspicion.

148
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:15,970
What?

149
00:08:15,970 --> 00:08:17,440
Dad went to Dream Hotel...

150
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:19,040
to meet CEO Chae?

151
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:20,140
Yes.

152
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,910
But it looks like
he never got to meet her.

153
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,940
So that's why he left
with those side dishes.

154
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:29,710
But if Dad didn't get to meet CEO Chae,

155
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:33,050
then what happened to those side dishes?
And his phone is still missing.

156
00:08:38,690 --> 00:08:39,790
Yes, CEO Chae.

157
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,190
I've been trying to reach you.

158
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:43,960
This must be hard for you, Jang Mi.

159
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:45,560
My goodness.

160
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:48,630
How could that have happened
to your father?

161
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:51,470
I'm just so devastated.

162
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:55,910
I know. I didn't find out
until the police stopped by this morning.

163
00:08:56,610 --> 00:08:59,140
So how is your father doing now?

164
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,650
He's not doing well at all.

165
00:09:01,810 --> 00:09:02,850
But...

166
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,220
according to the police,

167
00:09:05,220 --> 00:09:07,790
the last person my dad spoke to was me,

168
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:10,090
but they said you were the person
he spoke to right before me.

169
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:13,660
Did he happen to say anything to you?

170
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:16,290
I didn't see him in person.
We just spoke on the phone.

171
00:09:16,690 --> 00:09:18,800
It wasn't anything important.

172
00:09:19,430 --> 00:09:22,670
I was in a meeting,
so I just told him I'd call him back.

173
00:09:24,070 --> 00:09:26,340
I didn't even know he had come by.

174
00:09:26,870 --> 00:09:27,870
So...

175
00:09:28,540 --> 00:09:30,740
Is he in really bad shape?

176
00:09:32,210 --> 00:09:33,910
The surgery went well,

177
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:35,810
but he has a severe head injury.

178
00:09:36,610 --> 00:09:37,920
They said tonight was critical.

179
00:09:39,950 --> 00:09:41,120
That's terrible.

180
00:09:41,950 --> 00:09:45,020
Your father doted on you so much.

181
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:48,660
You and your family must be devastated.

182
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:54,970
Jang Mi, I have a meeting,
so I can't talk long.

183
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,470
Try not to worry too much.

184
00:09:58,100 --> 00:10:00,100
I'm sure your father will be all right.

185
00:10:01,110 --> 00:10:02,270
I'll call you later.

186
00:10:05,710 --> 00:10:06,710
That's a relief.

187
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,950
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

188
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:10,080
What about the police?

189
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:12,320
It looks like they'll rule it an accident.

190
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:16,090
Now, if Oh Bok Gil would just die,

191
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:18,490
this whole thing
would be wrapped up neatly.

192
00:10:20,830 --> 00:10:21,830
Are you going to go see him?

193
00:10:24,130 --> 00:10:25,160
Where are you going?

194
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,270
Do you do nothing
but follow me around all day?

195
00:10:28,530 --> 00:10:30,000
I told you to learn the ropes
from General Manager Kang...

196
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,240
and get him on your side.

197
00:10:31,340 --> 00:10:33,900
Why are you so snappy?
You told me not to be so aggressive.

198
00:10:33,970 --> 00:10:35,570
It starts now.

199
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:38,910
Try not to get on anyone's bad side.

200
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,310
Just keep your head down and do your work.

201
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,610
- Let's go.
- Yes, ma'am.

202
00:10:44,450 --> 00:10:45,450
What?

203
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:54,760
She won't let me say a thing.
Why is she so on edge?

204
00:10:55,990 --> 00:10:58,500
Did you hide it well? The wrench, I mean.

205
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:03,530
There must have been
some kind of accident.

206
00:11:04,870 --> 00:11:06,140
I need to look into this.

207
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:22,190
Just die already.

208
00:11:23,050 --> 00:11:24,390
Can't you see that...

209
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:28,290
Jung Suk Hee and Oh Jang Mi
will be in danger if you stay alive?

210
00:11:29,590 --> 00:11:32,260
Stop clinging to life and just die. Die!

211
00:11:38,940 --> 00:11:40,340
Why the hospital all of a sudden?

212
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:44,180
I'm sure she went that way.

213
00:11:46,410 --> 00:11:48,110
Bok Gil is hurt.

214
00:11:48,610 --> 00:11:50,410
Bok Gil is hurt.

215
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:54,350
Mom, you can't cry too much
in front of Dad.

216
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:57,090
Even if he's not conscious,
he can still hear everything, you know.

217
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:59,990
Okay, Suk Hee won't cry.

218
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,760
Suk Hee is sad.

219
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:05,400
Bok Gil is hurt.

220
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,910
Is that Manager Lee?

221
00:12:16,170 --> 00:12:17,270
Is he sick?

222
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:21,380
Okay, let's go, Mom.

223
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:41,870
Chae Hwa Young! It was you, wasn't it?

224
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,740
You tried to kill my Suk Hee
and Jang Mi, didn't you?

225
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:47,540
Why? Just tell me why!

226
00:12:48,970 --> 00:12:50,110
You asked me why?

227
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:52,410
Because it's the only way I can survive.

228
00:12:53,310 --> 00:12:54,410
Thirty years ago,

229
00:12:54,910 --> 00:12:58,550
if Jung Suk Hee and Oh Jang Mi had died,
none of this would've happened.

230
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:02,550
Why didn't you just die on that road?
Why are you still alive?

231
00:13:50,570 --> 00:13:54,070
(Intensive Care Unit)

232
00:13:59,410 --> 00:14:02,010
The doctor said the injury could be
from the accident.

233
00:14:05,650 --> 00:14:06,650
The doctor said that?

234
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:10,720
That the head trauma could be consistent
with the impact from the accident?

235
00:14:11,460 --> 00:14:12,460
Yes.

236
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,360
What a relief...

237
00:14:14,860 --> 00:14:17,230
that the wrench didn't leave a trace.

238
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:20,430
- Let's go.
- Yes, ma'am.

239
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,730
(Intensive Care Unit)

240
00:14:24,970 --> 00:14:26,440
Hit with a wrench?

241
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:31,240
(Intensive Care Unit)

242
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,040
(Intensive Care Unit)

243
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:44,390
That man...

244
00:14:45,060 --> 00:14:47,520
Hey! Who on earth is Jang Mi?

245
00:14:48,430 --> 00:14:49,460
Tell me.

246
00:14:49,460 --> 00:14:52,400
Why does everyone I meet keep confusing me
with this Jang Mi person?

247
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:54,030
I'm sorry.

248
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:56,230
It's just that you look so much
like my daughter.

249
00:14:57,740 --> 00:14:58,740
What's going on?

250
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:01,710
What's Mom's connection to this man?

251
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:09,810
(Intensive Care Unit)

252
00:15:43,450 --> 00:15:44,450
Dad.

253
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:47,320
- Are you okay?
- Do I look okay?

254
00:15:47,990 --> 00:15:50,890
This is a total disaster,
completely out of the blue.

255
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:56,130
Is it true the victim was lying
in the middle of the road?

256
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:05,300
Oh, no...

257
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:11,310
I gave the dashcam footage to the police.

258
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:16,050
You'll see from the video
that it was completely unavoidable.

259
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:17,850
When you went to check on him,

260
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,720
did you notice anything else strange?

261
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:22,190
Strange?

262
00:16:23,850 --> 00:16:24,960
Hey!

263
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,760
He reeks of alcohol.

264
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:30,660
Smells like he bathed in alcohol.

265
00:16:30,660 --> 00:16:32,730
He reeked of alcohol.

266
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,600
That's strange.

267
00:16:35,030 --> 00:16:37,800
From what I know,
Jang Mi's father can't hold his liquor.

268
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:41,570
His limit is half a bottle of rice wine,
and he said he couldn't drink soju at all.

269
00:16:42,570 --> 00:16:45,740
- What?
- And he had no reason to be there.

270
00:16:46,510 --> 00:16:48,810
Why would he suddenly go there by himself?

271
00:16:49,450 --> 00:16:50,950
And who was he drinking with?

272
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:52,580
None of it makes any sense.

273
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:53,950
Wait a minute.

274
00:16:53,950 --> 00:16:56,690
Did you just say Jang Mi's father?

275
00:16:57,250 --> 00:17:00,160
Didn't you say the name of that shady girl
you're seeing is Jang Mi?

276
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:03,990
Wait, so the man in the accident
is her father?

277
00:17:07,630 --> 00:17:08,630
Unbelievable.

278
00:17:14,610 --> 00:17:18,140
Thanks to you, Manager Lee,
it looks like everything went smoothly.

279
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:22,910
There's no way Oh Bok Gil will wake up
from his coma,

280
00:17:23,610 --> 00:17:26,020
and he's got one foot in the grave now.

281
00:17:26,350 --> 00:17:27,350
That's right.

282
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:30,490
The police investigation
is just a formality anyway.

283
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,960
I figured if we changed
secretaries’ work logs and CCTV,

284
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:34,530
we'd be fine.

285
00:17:35,190 --> 00:17:37,460
Plus, our story
about Oh Bok Gil's head injury worked out.

286
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:39,600
Good.

287
00:17:41,870 --> 00:17:43,700
I'm so glad I have you on my side.

288
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:47,070
We're pretty much wrapped up, right?

289
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:51,310
What a weight off my shoulders.

290
00:17:56,010 --> 00:17:58,620
Did you hide it well? The wrench, I mean.

291
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,020
Is the weapon...

292
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,620
the wrench Mom mentioned?

293
00:18:04,790 --> 00:18:07,590
Mom hit that man over the head
with the wrench.

294
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:09,560
No, it can't be.

295
00:18:10,630 --> 00:18:12,000
What is this, some kind of crime novel?

296
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:13,800
There's no way my mom
would do something like that.

297
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,130
But then why did she see that man
and just walk away?

298
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:20,470
And why does she keep lying to me?

299
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:25,140
And why did it have to be that man
in the car accident?

300
00:18:26,140 --> 00:18:28,550
It was the man who said
I looked just like his daughter.

301
00:18:34,050 --> 00:18:35,050
Don't tell me...

302
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:37,620
Does Mom know that man...

303
00:18:38,260 --> 00:18:41,330
is raising a girl named Jang Mi
who looks just like me?

304
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:44,500
Is that why she tried to kill him
with the wrench, and...

305
00:18:45,260 --> 00:18:46,330
No.

306
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:49,300
But then what about the car accident?

307
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,940
It was reported as a car accident.

308
00:18:57,740 --> 00:18:58,880
(Car Accident on Highway to Taean)

309
00:18:58,940 --> 00:19:00,040
(Leaves a Man in His 50s,
Mr. Oh, in Critical Condition)

310
00:19:09,090 --> 00:19:10,750
Is this Dream News?

311
00:19:11,660 --> 00:19:14,290
I'm calling about an accident report
from a few days ago...

312
00:19:18,660 --> 00:19:21,230
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

313
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,300
By the way, Kang Hyuk.

314
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:26,840
What did you do with the wrench?

315
00:19:26,970 --> 00:19:28,410
I buried it on a nearby mountain.

316
00:19:28,670 --> 00:19:29,670
On a mountain?

317
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:31,640
He buried it on a mountain?

318
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,740
I took care of it, so please don't worry.

319
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,080
No one will ever find it.

320
00:19:36,450 --> 00:19:39,980
Good. In any case,
that's the crucial piece of evidence,

321
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:42,190
so we have to make sure it's never found.

322
00:19:42,450 --> 00:19:43,990
Yes, I'm well aware.

323
00:19:47,490 --> 00:19:49,460
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

324
00:19:49,530 --> 00:19:51,500
(Law Firm Leeho)

325
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:54,300
Baek Ho, did you find anything out?

326
00:19:55,570 --> 00:19:58,700
Well, we have to wait for the results
to know for sure.

327
00:20:00,870 --> 00:20:04,110
So, what's your relationship
with the victim?

328
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:06,640
Your friend's dad, you said. Who is he?

329
00:20:06,780 --> 00:20:07,780
He's...

330
00:20:10,650 --> 00:20:13,320
- Jang Mi's father, Mom.
- What?

331
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:14,520
My dad...

332
00:20:15,850 --> 00:20:17,820
did this to the father of Jang Mi,

333
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:19,490
the woman I love.

334
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:22,090
My goodness.

335
00:20:24,660 --> 00:20:27,560
I can't believe it.
What a terrible twist of fate.

336
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,470
This is so upsetting.

337
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:34,270
I should've separated you ages ago
from that girl Jang Mi.

338
00:20:35,340 --> 00:20:36,970
Now your poor father is the one suffering.

339
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:39,580
Mom, do you really have to
put it that way?

340
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:43,210
The head of their household's life
is on the line right now.

341
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:45,550
I know Dad is going through a lot,
but how can you even...

342
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:47,950
compare his situation to theirs?

343
00:20:49,090 --> 00:20:51,560
I'm just saying it because I'm so upset.

344
00:20:53,290 --> 00:20:56,030
We need to get them to settle,
no matter what.

345
00:20:57,330 --> 00:20:58,430
This is a disaster.

346
00:21:04,170 --> 00:21:05,200
Manager Lee!

347
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:07,670
Hold on a second.

348
00:21:08,470 --> 00:21:12,810
What was the name of that restaurant
I went to with Mom last weekend?

349
00:21:13,380 --> 00:21:14,480
Let me check the navigation history.

350
00:21:15,110 --> 00:21:16,250
Sure, go ahead.

351
00:21:24,860 --> 00:21:25,920
(Recent Destinations)

352
00:21:25,990 --> 00:21:27,360
(Dream Hotel, 55 Hoseon-ro,
Hangang-gu, Seoul)

353
00:21:35,770 --> 00:21:38,700
(21-ro, Yeongseo-myeon)

354
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:41,240
Yes.

355
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:44,210
Did you say Route 21 in Yeongseo-myeon,
toward Taean?

356
00:21:47,380 --> 00:21:50,250
Here it is.
It's that really good Chinese place.

357
00:21:51,210 --> 00:21:52,220
Is it?

358
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:03,390
- I'm leaving.
- Okay.

359
00:22:04,260 --> 00:22:05,260
Bye.

360
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,750
Mom.

361
00:22:26,350 --> 00:22:28,190
Why on earth would you do that
to Oh Jang Mi's father?

362
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:32,990
Are you even the mother I thought I knew?

363
00:22:33,990 --> 00:22:35,190
Are you?

364
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:46,370
Come on, eat something.

365
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:54,410
You've done nothing but drink for days.
You look terrible.

366
00:22:56,150 --> 00:22:58,520
The person you hit with your car
was Oh Jang Mi's...

367
00:22:59,620 --> 00:23:03,750
You know, the man from that side dish shop
Baek Ho is obsessed with.

368
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:07,460
- Did you know that?
- Yes, Baek Ho told me.

369
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:12,430
Wait, you've been to the side dish shop,
so you must have met him.

370
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:13,700
I did more than just meet him.

371
00:23:14,660 --> 00:23:18,400
I just told him to talk some sense
into his daughter,

372
00:23:18,770 --> 00:23:20,270
and he had the nerve
to start lecturing me.

373
00:23:21,140 --> 00:23:24,940
He said Baek Ho was after his daughter,
so I should be the one talking to my son.

374
00:23:27,210 --> 00:23:29,610
So I guess a settlement
is out of the question, right?

375
00:23:30,180 --> 00:23:32,850
No, that can't happen.
Before something bad happens to him,

376
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:34,520
we have to get them to settle.

377
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:37,250
Something bad?

378
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:40,520
My office manager met with the doctor,

379
00:23:41,790 --> 00:23:43,030
and the doctor said there’s no hope
for his recovery.

380
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:55,270
You're not Jang Mi.

381
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:57,610
You're pretending to be Jang Mi.

382
00:23:57,610 --> 00:23:58,880
You're not Jang Mi.

383
00:23:59,310 --> 00:24:00,340
I'm sorry.

384
00:24:00,810 --> 00:24:02,380
It's just that you look so much
like my daughter.

385
00:24:03,750 --> 00:24:05,450
I haven't found any proof yet,

386
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:08,750
but I'm sure my mom was
at the scene of the accident.

387
00:24:10,050 --> 00:24:11,050
Okay, first things first.

388
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:13,460
I need to figure out
who this woman, Jang Mi, is,

389
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:15,490
the one who looks just like me.

390
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,570
It was so nice to get some fresh air.

391
00:24:29,740 --> 00:24:31,810
Goodness, I'm exhausted.

392
00:24:31,810 --> 00:24:34,140
Oh my, you must be exhausted, Chairman.

393
00:24:34,580 --> 00:24:36,380
Go on in and get some rest, okay?

394
00:24:38,050 --> 00:24:40,920
- You're home, Seo Rin.
- Yes, but I'm heading out again.

395
00:24:40,950 --> 00:24:41,990
Where to?

396
00:24:42,120 --> 00:24:44,820
Once you're home for the night,
you're supposed to wash up and go to bed.

397
00:24:44,890 --> 00:24:48,060
Don't give me that kind of speech.
I'll be back, Grandpa.

398
00:24:56,470 --> 00:24:58,340
If I want to meet this Jang Mi woman,

399
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:01,240
I'm sure I can find her
at that man's hospital room.

400
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:16,220
(Korea University Hospital)

401
00:25:41,510 --> 00:25:42,580
What's going on?

402
00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:44,380
Why am I over there?

403
00:25:49,090 --> 00:25:50,350
Dad...

404
00:25:55,060 --> 00:25:56,090
That's me.

405
00:25:56,790 --> 00:25:59,830
Why am I over there?
How can I be over there?

406
00:26:02,670 --> 00:26:03,870
Am I dead?

407
00:26:04,670 --> 00:26:06,470
Is that why my soul separated
from my body?

408
00:26:10,940 --> 00:26:11,940
No, that can't be it.

409
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:21,690
I'm afraid...

410
00:26:22,390 --> 00:26:24,490
you need to prepare for the worst
for Mr. Oh Bok Gil.

411
00:26:25,660 --> 00:26:26,790
Dad.

412
00:26:49,850 --> 00:26:51,010
No.

413
00:27:05,860 --> 00:27:06,860
Wait a minute.

414
00:27:07,860 --> 00:27:09,100
Her name is Jang Mi, right?

415
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:11,330
Oh Jang Mi, I really need to talk to you.

416
00:27:11,770 --> 00:27:15,040
How on earth do you look exactly like me?
Who are you?

417
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:23,750
Where did she go?

418
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:41,360
(The First Man)

419
00:27:41,430 --> 00:27:44,930
Detective, did you have any luck
finding Jang Mi's father's cell phone?

420
00:27:45,270 --> 00:27:48,140
This might just be the crucial evidence.

421
00:27:49,340 --> 00:27:51,210
You want me to get them to settle?

422
00:27:51,370 --> 00:27:54,210
Is Oh Jang Mi more important to you
than your own dad?

423
00:27:54,540 --> 00:27:57,450
So Professor Kang Nam Bong was the one
who hit Jang Mi's dad?

424
00:27:57,650 --> 00:27:59,950
How's our Jun Ho's office coming along?

425
00:27:59,950 --> 00:28:01,120
"Our" Jun Ho?

426
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:03,590
Do we really need to have secrets
between us?

427
00:28:03,850 --> 00:28:06,460
I suppose there's no reason
to hide it from you.

428
00:28:06,890 --> 00:28:08,290
Kang Jun Ho is my son.

429
00:28:13,060 --> 00:28:15,070
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
